<p>This simulation shows how distances are calculated from vertex D to all =
other vertices, by always choosing the next vertex to be the closest unvisi=
ted vertex from the starting point.</p>
<p>Follow the step-by-step description below to get all the details of how =
Dijkstra's algorithm calculates the shortest distances.</p>
