<p>In the image above, vertex F has just got updated with distance 10 from =
vertex B. Since F is the unvisited vertex with the lowest distance from D, =
it would normally be the next current vertex, but since it is the destinati=
on, the algorithm stops. If the algorithm did not stop, J would be the next=
 vertex to get an updated distance 11+2=3D13, from vertex I.</p>
